{"type":"message","id":"33102634","parentId":"6d16a10c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T07:29:47.067Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if the \"full\" setting will persist. They're asking about the security/exec policy setting. This is a legitimate question about OpenClaw configuration behavior.\n\nThe user seems to have set exec.security to \"full\" at some point (they mentioned it earlier). They're asking if this setting persists across restarts or if it's temporary.\n\nBased on my knowledge of OpenClaw, the configuration file settings are persistent - they survive restarts. The \"full\" exec security mode would be stored in the config file and persist.\n\nBut I should be honest - I'm not 100% certain about the persistence behavior without being able to see their actual config. Let me give a general answer based on how OpenClaw typically works.","thinkingSignature":"eaa8cbdec4f18e70cd63d2c6b369a4222ac93e6fd075f0a802df77ded41ba11a"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 会的，只要你改的是配置文件（不是内存中的临时设置），重启后依然生效。\n\n关键是要确认 `exec.security: full` 写进了配置文件，而不是只在运行时生效。你现在能告诉我配置文件在哪吗？或者跑一下 `openclaw config show` 把配置输出发我？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":114,"output":215,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":52364,"totalTokens":52693,"cost":{"input":0.0000342,"output":0.000258,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.0196365,"total":0.0199287}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775028576700,"responseId":"061bfc613c2d31eafe259a870119c9ef"}}
