{"type":"message","id":"76099830","parentId":"27a8ed26","timestamp":"2026-04-01T07:32:06.063Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7bmkyve89sos_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This screenshot displays the help menu for a command-line interface (CLI) tool called **OpenClaw**, version 2026.3.31 (213a704). The tool's tagline is \"I'm the middleware between your ambition and your attention span.\"\n\nThe menu details the tool's usage, global options, and available commands.\n\n### **Usage Syntax**\n`openclaw [options] [command]`\n\n### **Options**\nThe following global flags are available to modify the behavior of any command:\n*   `--container <name>`: Runs the CLI inside a specified Podman/Docker container.\n*   `--dev`: Activates a developer profile with isolated state and specific port shifts for browser/canvas.\n*   `-h, --help`: Displays help for a command.\n*   `--log-level <level>`: Sets the global log level (silent, fatal, error, warn, info, debug, or trace).\n*   `--no-color`: Disables ANSI color output.\n*   `--profile <name>`: Uses a named profile to isolate state and configuration directories.\n*   `-V, --version`: Outputs the version number.\n\n### **Commands**\nOpenClaw features an extensive list of commands, many of which have subcommands (indicated by an asterisk `*`). Key functional areas include:\n\n*   **Agent Management**: `agent` (run a turn), `agents` (manage isolated agents), `hooks` (internal agent hooks).\n*   **System & Configuration**: `configure` (interactive setup), `config` (non-interactive helpers), `onboard` (interactive onboarding), `reset` (reset local state), `doctor` (health checks and quick fixes).\n*   **Communication Channels**: `channels` (Telegram, Discord, etc.), `openclaw-weixin` (Weixin utilities), `message` (send/read messages), `directory` (contact lookup).\n*   **Network & Infrastructure**: `gateway` (WebSocket gateway management), `node` / `nodes` (headless node host service), `dns` (Tailscale + CoreDNS discovery), `pairing` (secure DM pairing).\n*   **Security & Data**: `approvals` (execution approvals), `secrets` (runtime reload controls), `backup` (create/verify state archives), `sandbox` (container isolation for agents).\n*   **Miscellaneous**: `dashboard` (opens Control UI), `models` (discover and configure models), `mcp` (Model Context Protocol config), `memory` (search and reindex files), `cron` (manage scheduled jobs), `qr` (generate iOS setup codes).\n*   **Diagnostics**: Includes a specific Chinese-language command `feishu-diagnose` for diagnosing Feishu plugin configurations."}],"details":{"model":"minimax/MiniMax-VL-01","image":"/home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/2cebd3f8-cd64-4211-80ad-a97313216e2a.jpg","attempts":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775028725616}}
