{"type":"message","id":"eb00dab3","parentId":"5b1e987d","timestamp":"2026-04-01T08:32:22.315Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to tell them which setting in the backend (dashboard) to change to enable full mode. Based on what we discussed earlier, they need to set `exec.security` to `full` in their OpenClaw config. \n\nBut the user is asking specifically about the dashboard UI. Looking at the openclaw help output I got earlier, there's a `dashboard` command that \"opens Control UI\". \n\nSince I can't take screenshots myself, I should explain what they need to do - either:\n1. Find the exec.security setting in the dashboard and set it to \"full\"\n2. Or edit the config file manually\n\nLet me give them clear instructions on what to look for in the dashboard.","thinkingSignature":"ffed4932b6bcecfd1653255bfcc5247a76d0d0d6ff2e27a1ffe9d4b28a33ff23"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 在后台（dashboard）里找这个设置：\n\n**`exec.security`** → 改成 **`full`**\n\n一般在：\n- `设置(Settings)` → `安全(Security)` → `Exec Security`\n- 或者直接搜 `security`\n\n找不到就把 `exec.security` 改成 `full` 然后保存。\n\n---\n\n**备选方案**：直接改配置文件。运行：\n\n```bash\nopenclaw config show\n```\n\n把输出发我，我告诉你具体改哪一行。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":114,"output":247,"cacheRead":147898,"cacheWrite":608,"totalTokens":148867,"cost":{"input":0.0000342,"output":0.0002964,"cacheRead":0.008873879999999999,"cacheWrite":0.000228,"total":0.00943248}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775032328952,"responseId":"061c0b093918c03f3210038dd30eec8d"}}
